    <p style="margin-left: 8; margin-right: 8"><font size="2"><font face="Microsoft Sans Serif" size="2">

<font size=2><table width="100%" bgcolor="#004b97"><font color=#d2d200><b>Jiva</b></font>&nbsp;&nbsp;<font size=1><a style="color: #ffffff" href="mailto:jcsmith@amazinghideaways.com?subject=Regarding: Jiva">Submit Info</a></font></table>
<font color=white>
<br><img align="right" src="http://www.amazinghideaways.com/uploads/eqbestiary/Jiva/picture/efreetinabil.jpg">
<b><font color=#d2d200>Level:</font></b> 68-68<br>
<b><font color=#d2d200>Sociality:</b></font> Social<br>
<b><font color=#d2d200>Classification:</b></font> Rare_Monster<br>
<b><font color=#d2d200>Known Habitats:</b></font> Tower of Solusek Ro<br>









<br><b><font color=#d2d200>Description:</b></font><br>- Boss of the middle fork.<BR>- Fire based PBAE (-300) does 500 points of damage and lowers your ATK by 50 for one tick. It has a recast of 20 seconds.<BR>- Spawns adds at set intervals of time during the fight. The longer the fight goes, the more adds will come. So DPS is important.<BR>- Magic Slowable<BR><BR><b>Spawn and Scouting</b><BR><BR>A rogue can scout Jiva by porting up to her tower (middle tower) with SoS. Tracking is not a viable option and Eye's of Zomm will likely not have the duration to reach Jiva's tower.<BR><BR>Jiva is a 3 day spawn.<BR><BR><b>What You Need</b><BR><BR>Jiva can be killed with 18-24 players, depending on their gear and make-up. You will want 2-3 enchanters and at least four clerics and a good tank. If you are low on DPS or encanters then you will want to bring 30+.<BR><BR><b>Preparation</b><BR><BR>You will want to MGB fire resistance buffs for this fight. Jiva's AE will do 1500 points of damager every minute, and also lowers everyones ATK by 50 points. It's more annoying than dangerous, but there's no reason not to try to minimize it's effect.<BR><BR>You will also likely want to have at least one druid save MGB for Spirit of the Wood during the fight. If you are low on DPS you might want them all to save it.<BR><BR><b>Getting to Jiva</b><BR><BR>Jiva is located in the middle tower. His tower is the second largest (after the Protector of Dresolik) but is relatively easy. None of the rooms in this tower are as difficult to split as those in Dresolik, Arlyxir or Rizlona's towers. It should be easy to pull two or three at a time.<BR><BR><b>The Fight</b><BR><BR>Jiva is tethered to the small platform in the middle of his room. It is important that before you engage everyone undersetands that you need to jump on to this platform using the small steps on the sides. He will not pull down from here. Everyone should also already have fire resistance buffs prior to engaging to aid on his PBAE. His PBAE is fire based (-300) and does 500 points of damage and lowers your ATK by 50 for one tick. It has a recast of 20 seconds. Casting Spirit of the Wood after the first AE hits will all but nullify it.<BR><BR>It is important that everyone is ready to rush him at the same time and does not aggro him before you are ready. As soon as he is aggroed he will begin to spawn adds at the rate of one every 24 seconds or so. They will spawn in order from the entrances around his room. Two or three enchanters should be able to manage these adds without difficulties unless your DPS is really bad. Kill him quickly and the you won't receive more than a few adds during the fight. After he is dead you can clean up the adds.<BR><BR>A four cleric healing chain should be sufficient for Jiva.<BR><BR><b>Getting Flagged</b><BR><BR>After killing Jiva and handling loot everyone needs to go through the door behind his room and click the brazier to exit the tower. This completes the flag. You have about 30 minutes after killing him to port down, so you take your time on assigning loot.<BR><BR>It is very important that nobody tries to enter or exit his chamber from the way that you entered, or else they will die to a trap that becomes active when he is killed. This is to prevent players from running in and mooching the flag.<BR><BR><b>Loot</b><BR><BR>Jiva drops two items per kill and his items are better than those of most lower-tier gods. The Rune Etched Bamboo Stick is one of the best monk/beastlord two-handers in the game. The Black Basalt Band is fantastic for any melee class, the Jagged Shard of Flame is a great aggro and DPS weapon and the Ornate Broadsword is a very respectable paladin only one-hander. For this reason he is often killed as an early or late raid by elemental guilds. <br>

<br><b>Known Drops</b>:<br>

<A HREF="webdata_pro%2epl?_cgifunction=Search&_layout=equipmentfull&eqequipment%2eitem_name=%22Rune Etched Bamboo Bo%22">Rune Etched Bamboo Bo</A><br> <A HREF="webdata_pro%2epl?_cgifunction=Search&_layout=equipmentfull&eqequipment%2eitem_name=%22Black Basalt Band%22">Black Basalt Band</A><br> <A HREF="webdata_pro%2epl?_cgifunction=Search&_layout=equipmentfull&eqequipment%2eitem_name=%22Jagged Shard of Frozen Flame%22">Jagged Shard of Frozen Flame</A><br> <A HREF="webdata_pro%2epl?_cgifunction=Search&_layout=equipmentfull&eqequipment%2eitem_name=%22Ornate Broadsword%22">Ornate Broadsword</A><br>

